    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>The collection contains the manuscripts for the following poems and short stories:  <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="doublequote" xlink:href="">Old ace,</title><title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="doublequote" xlink:href="">Dead dancer,</title><title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="doublequote" xlink:href="">Continuous performance,</title><title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="doublequote" xlink:href="">The husbandman [A green bough],</title><title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="doublequote" xlink:href="">L'apres-midi d'un faune,</title><title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="doublequote" xlink:href="">The lilacs,</title><title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="doublequote" xlink:href="">Music dying languidly in darkness,</title> and <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="doublequote" xlink:href="">One way to catch a horse,</title> as well as untitled fragments and a brief outline for parts of <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">Sanctuary.</title>  The collection also contains several sketches including a Japanese woman, soldiers and an airplane; and <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="doublequote" xlink:href="">Landing in luck,</title> as printed in the <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">Oxford Eagle</title> (Miss.) in 1919.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement>
      <head>Arrangement</head>
      <p>The collection is in two series : I. Manuscripts. II.
         Miscellaneous</p>
    </arrangement>
